Aedeagus small (
0.27 mm
), with trifid apex (

Fig. 
9

), subrectangular in lateral view (

Fig. 
10

). Medial piece composed of a broad base and of long and thin apical prominence, with serrate margins. Parameres thin, concave towards the medial piece, each of them bearing six long marginal setae. Basal piece of the aedeagus subcylindrical, connected to the apical pieces by a ring-shaped articulation. Aedeagus connected to a suboval internal sclerite, ciliated along the distal margin (

